<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1265,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1713,1739]" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Notes:</emphasis>
About 9 species of 
<taxonomicName box="[489,584,1714,1740]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,584,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Asterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been described on 
<taxonomicName box="[861,967,1714,1740]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Syzygium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,967,1714,1740]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Syzygium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the world (
<bibRefCitation author="Hosagoudar, V. B. &amp; Abraham, T. K." pageId="1" pageNumber="284" pagination="557 - 587" refId="ref3225" refString="Hosagoudar, V. B. &amp; Abraham, T. K. (2000) A list of Asterina Lev. species based on the literature. Journal of Economic &amp; Taxonomic Botany 24: 557 - 587." type="journal article" year="2000">Hosagoudar and Abraham 2000</bibRefCitation>
, Far and Rossman 2014, Patil 
<emphasis box="[573,643,1751,1777]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">et. al.</emphasis>
2014). The present species was found in association with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kar &amp; Maity (1970: 438)" authorityName="Kar &amp; Maity" authorityPageNumber="438" authorityYear="1970" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="jambolanae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Asterina jambolanae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kar, A. K. &amp; Maity, M. K." box="[279,570,1788,1815]" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" pagination="435 - 444" refId="ref3306" refString="Kar, A. K. &amp; Maity, M. K. (1970) New Asterina species from West Bengal. Transactions of the British Mycological Society 54: 435 - 444." type="journal article" year="1970">Kar &amp; Maity (1970:438)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in having unicellular appressoria instead of the bicellular ones. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bhise &amp; Patil &amp; Salunkhe" authorityYear="2014" box="[136,386,1826,1852]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="myrtacearum">
<emphasis box="[136,386,1826,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Asterina myrtacearum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Nair &amp; Kaul (1987: 1071)" authorityName="Nair &amp; Kaul (1987:" authorityPageNumber="1071" authorityYear="1071" box="[535,1117,1825,1852]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gopalakrishnanii">
<emphasis box="[535,827,1825,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Asterina gopalakrishnanii</emphasis>
Nair &amp; Kaul (1987:1071)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Patil, Bhise &amp; Patil (2014: 81)" authorityName="Patil, Bhise &amp; Patil" authorityPageNumber="81" authorityYear="2014" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lanceolatae">
<emphasis box="[1129,1290,1825,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">A. lanceolatae</emphasis>
Patil, Bhise &amp; Patil (2014:81)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kar &amp; Maity (1970: 441)" authorityName="Kar &amp; Maity" authorityPageNumber="441" authorityYear="1970" box="[361,781,1863,1889]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="claviflori">
<emphasis box="[361,496,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">A. claviflori</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kar, A. K. &amp; Maity, M. K." box="[504,781,1863,1889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" pagination="435 - 444" refId="ref3306" refString="Kar, A. K. &amp; Maity, M. K. (1970) New Asterina species from West Bengal. Transactions of the British Mycological Society 54: 435 - 444." type="journal article" year="1970">Kar &amp; Maity (1970:441)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
known on 
<taxonomicName box="[909,1069,1863,1889]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Syzygium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[909,1015,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">Syzygium</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
in having unicellular appressoria, however, it differs in having dense epiphyllous colonies with distinctly flexuous to crooked mycelium; larger size of appressoria, thyriothecia and ascospores; as well as distinctly smooth walled ascospores in contrast to spiny and verrucose walled in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nair &amp; Kaul (1987:" authorityYear="1071" box="[354,574,1975,2001]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gopalakrishnanii">
<emphasis box="[354,574,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="284">A. gopalakrishnanii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kar &amp; Maity" authorityYear="1970" box="[623,755,1975,2001]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Asterinaceae" genus="Asterina" kingdom="Fungi" order="Asterinales" pageId="1" pageNumber="284" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="claviflori">
